	<para>To launch an editor and begin entering text:</para>
    <variablelist>
	<varlistentry>
	<term>Select the [Launcher] key.</term>
	<listitem>
	<para>This will branch you to the &app; Launcher keyboard.</para>
	</listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry>
	<term>Select [Text Editor]</term>
	<listitem>
	<para>This will cause a text editor to be launched, and GOK should automatically branch to the Main keyboard.</para>
	</listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry>
	<term>Select [Compose]</term>
	<listitem>
	<para>This will branch you to a keyboard which will allow you to enter text in the editor application.</para>
	</listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	</variablelist>
    </sect2>
     <sect2 id="gok-when-docked">
    <title>Docking &app;</title>
    <para><application>&app;</application> functions well as a docked window.</para>
	<para>You can dock <application>&app;</application> via the preferences dialog, or alternatively via the "window" keyboard.</para>
		<note>
	   		<para><application>&app;</application> will not function correctly if docked on the same edge as something else.</para>
		</note>
	</sect2>
